# No Fallbacks Ever

## Context
- When writing any code that handles data
- When parsing API responses or user input
- When implementing error handling or data processing

## Requirements
- NEVER add fallback values or defaults
- NEVER add protective "|| defaultValue" logic
- NEVER add try/catch blocks for "safety"
- Let code fail fast and loud with clear errors
- Use expected data structure directly
- No defensive programming patterns

## Examples
<example>
const name = data.name;
const amount = data.amount;
const items = data.receiptItems;
</example>

<example type="invalid">
const name = data.name || 'Default Name';
const amount = data.amount || 0;
const items = data.receiptItems || [];
</example>

## Critical Rules
- NEVER use || for fallback values
- NEVER add "safety" defaults
- Let it crash with useful errors
- No defensive programming ever
- Fail fast and loud